Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.70,0:00:04.35,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should use the same members \Nwe've been using for the next match.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:07.98,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should go without Desktomu-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.70,0:00:15.06,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  Why's that, Porky?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.06,0:00:17.99,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!  Why would you say that now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.46,0:00:21.67,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,It only makes sense for Desktomu-kun \Nto play in the playoffs!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.21,0:00:26.62,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be much more useful than \Nan exhausted Tsukuba-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:24.87,bingo,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.62,0:00:27.77,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.77,0:00:28.78,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kana-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.58,0:00:30.87,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.63,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Our next opponent is Shoyo \NHigh School from Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.34,0:00:37.68,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching Fujisaki's match,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:39.90,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't have much \Ninformation on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.36,0:00:41.39,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:45.06,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I talked to the team they \Nbeat and found out that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.39,0:00:47.35,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.97,0:00:49.86,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't you speak up?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.86,0:00:53.09,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you asking to be a starter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.06,0:00:56.44,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,We've worked so hard together!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.44,0:00:58.12,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you letting a new \Nmember take your spot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.96,0:01:04.78,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit that the first-years have \Ntaken some of the pressure off of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.82,0:01:07.04,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,but that's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:13.55,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You can't stop fighting to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.38,0:01:18.25,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've lost that drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.85,0:01:21.56,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,you'll start to lose your edge!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:27.35,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take Tsukuba any day when he's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.35,0:01:29.11,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,willing to rewrite the \Norder so he can play!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.11,0:01:29.86,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.37,0:01:32.10,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let the Prez decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.11,0:01:36.26,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Porky!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.68,0:01:46.05,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,What order do I go with?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.65,0:01:48.37,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Who do I play and who do I sit out?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.59,0:01:51.26,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand where \NNishida was coming from,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:55.27,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,but this isn't the mood we \Nwant before the playoffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.38,0:01:57.33,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.25,0:01:59.93,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi, give me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.90,0:02:03.23,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Shoyo from Kyoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.74,0:02:04.68,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.05,0:02:07.62,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Sano, Ooka, Kawabe, Tashiro, Sanada...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.62,0:02:08.70,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,They're all right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.70,0:02:10.40,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Two girls and three boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.58,0:02:10.40,Chiha-overlap,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.40,0:02:12.77,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,You should have lunch now \Nif you haven't eaten yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.23,0:02:14.78,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,We only have thirty minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.34,0:02:17.12,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}There aren't any vending \Nmachines, so here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.28,0:02:18.23,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,I need to be more proactive \Nas their advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.07,0:02:22.08,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,The advisor is supposed to \Ndecide on what order to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.84,0:02:24.56,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Especially when the going gets tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:30.08,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Ayase-san can only be counted \Non to play in matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.84,0:02:32.92,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,There's too much pressure on Mashima-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.32,0:02:35.63,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:38.57,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll rest Desktomu-kun and use
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.57,0:02:39.86,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the same five from the group stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:53.11,Chiha-title2,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1800)}Chihaya Furu
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:55.97,Chiha-ep-title-verse,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,900)}Verse 11
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:55.97,Chiha-ep-title-poem-wide,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,900)}I feel as\N though\N my body\Nis on fire \Nwith Ibuki \Nmugwort
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:03:58.88,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,What now? What now?! What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:02.88,curry,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Curry Rice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:02.39,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I have to say that \Nright before the playoffs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:04.13,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.13,0:04:05.19,Chiha-main,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Back again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.19,0:04:07.22,Chiha-main,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have a match coming up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:08.26,Chiha-main,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you won't regret this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.49,0:04:10.78,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I don't regret it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:13.78,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't say something now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:18.15,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun would drift \Ninto a supporting role.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:21.67,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't be one of \Nthe players anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.76,0:04:23.71,Chiha-main,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.71,0:04:24.49,Chiha-main,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Finish the whole plate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.63,0:04:26.93,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,But what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:33.06,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,If nobody does anything and he's \Nremoved from the lineup...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:39.76,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,And if that familiar-looking person \Nover there really is my sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:42.69,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Porky!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.45,0:04:45.47,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?! \N We've been looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.95,0:04:47.92,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The match is about to begin!  Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:51.72,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time for us to talk strategy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:54.40,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you in the cafeteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.40,0:04:55.98,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,We bought three lunches.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:04:59.54,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we'll be going with the same \Nlineup we used in the group stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.37,0:05:05.36,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Playoff teams, please head inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.88,0:05:07.22,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.22,0:05:09.12,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't want to play?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:10.62,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Porky!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.88,0:05:13.43,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,If you're matched up against \NKawabe, try to stay calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:14.37,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.65,0:05:17.25,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's just guessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.81,0:05:22.21,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:23.55,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.23,0:05:27.29,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Don't need your help...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:31.68,handwriting,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,2000)}Shoyo High School    Mizusawa High School
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.95,0:05:30.32,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The playoffs...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.71,0:05:34.90,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Featuring the eight schools \Nthat won their groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:37.31,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,One loss, and the team is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:42.98,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Our opponent is Shoyo High \NSchool, representing Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.72,0:05:46.32,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Show you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:47.96,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,Shoyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.96,0:05:49.31,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Shoyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.31,0:05:50.32,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,A pun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:53.44,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a coincidence that all their faces
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:55.14,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,resemble ancient officials in textbooks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:56.08,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Two minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:05:57.33,Chiha-main,Kawa,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this, Shoyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:58.55,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.22,0:06:01.16,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoto:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.77,0:06:03.56,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,where Wakamiya Shinobu is from.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.31,0:06:08.34,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,They look very imposing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.52,0:06:11.52,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Komano-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.14,0:06:13.26,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:14.99,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we tell you to get some rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.48,0:06:17.09,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,You should grab something to eat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.09,0:06:17.88,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:21.28,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.64,0:06:32.18,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Here comes spring, \Nnow the flower blooms
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.35,0:06:41.75,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Here comes spring, \Nnow the flower blooms
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:46.58,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Though I prayed to the god of mercy \Nthat the one I love not shun me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:47.35,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.82,0:06:48.83,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:51.58,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone from Kyoto this fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.12,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Like Wakamiya Shinobu?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:00.40,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,One loss in this tournament...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.37,0:07:03.70,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,and our team is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:09.07,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,May it be that I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:13.43,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.  Very bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:29.42,sleep,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1000)}Empress' \Njacket\Nof love
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.81,0:07:26.69,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,We should let him sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.50,0:07:29.42,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go see how the match is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:32.09,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Can you watch Komano-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.83,0:07:34.70,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to watch the match...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:36.72,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,You also need to get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:38.26,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.26,0:07:43.59,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,...summer night fully breaks
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.97,0:07:48.41,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,In the sleepy spring sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.41,0:07:49.38,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,He took another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:50.94,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,He's really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.33,0:07:54.62,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I have to stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.78,0:08:09.51,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll rest Desktomu-kun and use \Nthe same five from the group stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.51,0:08:10.30,Chiha-flashback,All,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:13.43,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Harada once taught me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.92,0:08:16.12,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,that you shouldn't \Nconcentrate on watching
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.12,0:08:18.31,Chiha-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,other people play before \Nyour own match begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.94,0:08:23.11,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,It's more tiring to closely watch \Na match than to play a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:25.47,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,After seeing this, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.43,0:08:29.76,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun is much more \Ntired than the rest of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:32.01,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm leaving him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:37.29,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,The storm blasts...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:39.41,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:42.33,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep up with his \Nsporadic bursts of speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.15,0:08:44.35,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,My arm won't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.93,0:08:47.41,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,This Kawabe guy is really good...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.90,0:08:49.74,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Kawabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.54,0:08:52.70,Chiha-flashback,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,If you're matched up against \NKawabe, try to stay calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.36,0:08:55.04,Chiha-flashback,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's just guessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.29,0:09:05.99,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,to set the Tatsuta River ablaze
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:09.11,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,After many, many years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:10.86,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Is this speed he's using the real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:14.94,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, I would have no trouble \Nprotecting the "After many" at my lower left,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.94,0:09:17.57,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,but he took it before I heard the "many."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.67,0:09:20.33,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Does he have good game sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:22.66,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:26.91,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He's gambling that his \Ncard will be read.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.34,0:09:38.62,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,now bloom inside the nine-fold palace
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.31,0:09:42.08,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,As I wait for someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.46,0:09:43.62,Chiha-internal,Kawa,0000,0000,0000,,A fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:47.03,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,A person with good game sense
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.03,0:09:49.28,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't let me goad \Nthem into that fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:52.15,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He's just guessing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.53,0:09:56.41,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.86,0:09:58.77,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.61,0:10:07.51,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,A mountain village grows \Nlonesome every winter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:09.25,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,According to Desktomu-kun's notes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.47,0:10:12.59,Chiha-main,Ta,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.73,0:10:16.12,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Tashiro-kun likes to stand up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.62,0:10:20.01,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He does this frequently \Nto get into a rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.39,0:10:22.30,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,So I should put an early stop to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:25.81,pout,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Pout
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:25.81,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,What?  You're standing up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:28.06,Chiha-main,Ta,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:32.75,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it harder for \NTashiro-kun to stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:35.63,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,I'm throwing him off his rhythm early on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.63,0:10:36.94,Chiha-internal,Ta,0000,0000,0000,,I should stand up again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:37.78,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.08,0:10:40.02,Chiha-main,Ooka,0000,0000,0000,,That card was mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:42.66,Chiha-main,Ooka,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't have flown in that \Ndirection if I hadn't hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:43.54,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.54,0:10:44.91,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely got that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:48.74,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Ooka will contest cards that she
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:51.29,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,obviously lost so she can cool down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:55.34,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,You and I both know \Nthat I won that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.81,0:10:57.50,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending this card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:03.14,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought that skill \Nwas everything in karuta.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:06.08,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought that data \Ncould be so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:08.03,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.66,0:11:13.15,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Sanada-san is a whacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.89,0:11:16.44,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,He whacks the tatami when \Nhe practices his swing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:18.67,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,but it doesn't scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.27,0:11:22.53,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It means his motions are rough and sloppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:25.99,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine how hard it was
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:28.21,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,for him to gather this \Ninformation from a team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.21,0:11:29.62,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,that just lost their match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:37.42,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.61,0:11:40.80,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to talk \Nto you about Shoyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:42.41,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.41,0:11:44.80,Chiha-internal,B,0000,0000,0000,,You should know how it feels to \Nwant the team who beat you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:46.52,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,to win the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.52,0:11:47.18,Chiha-internal,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.33,0:11:49.18,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I want...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:54.05,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do whatever I can \Nto support my teammates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.84,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you know how that feels!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.84,0:11:59.03,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,So please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.34,0:12:13.26,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun has the drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.26,0:12:19.23,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,That notebook is his way of \Nsaying that he wants Mizusawa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:20.89,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,to be first in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:24.54,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.32,0:12:28.98,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I fell asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:30.35,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,You scared me, senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:33.26,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell if you're awake or \Nasleep because of your glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:35.31,hello,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:34.94,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,What about the match?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:36.56,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's still going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.39,0:12:38.22,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:44.66,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's perfectly okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:45.57,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.13,0:12:48.30,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,You're so good at gathering data
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.30,0:12:50.73,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that it doesn't matter if you don't play!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:54.33,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to play in a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:55.85,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:12:59.10,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard and scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.36,0:13:02.72,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I got nervous when Porky called me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:07.47,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,We won!  Mizusawa won!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:15.44,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You're playing in the \Nnext match, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.71,0:13:20.22,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You're playing in the \Nnext match, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.22,0:13:21.48,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to join us, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:22.42,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Desktomu-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.37,0:13:48.33,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,We worked so hard to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.31,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,We want you with us as a player.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.81,0:14:05.78,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You should always be a player with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.83,0:14:13.52,Chiha-main,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,Arata!  I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:16.10,Chiha-main,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault you have \Nto write this essay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.10,0:14:18.29,Chiha-main,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,No, I should apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.29,0:14:19.88,Chiha-main,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can't return this T-shirt yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.45,0:14:23.63,Chiha-main,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,since I had to lend mine \Nto the drenched Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.65,0:14:23.63,jeans,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,And \Nthose \Npants
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.65,0:14:23.63,phone,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,And \Nthat \Nphone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:25.88,Chiha-main,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,That's no big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:27.55,Chiha-main,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,You can keep it if you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.80,0:14:30.11,Chiha-main,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, unless you don't want it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:34.56,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wataya-kun, what was \Nyour objective today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:35.22,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.80,0:14:38.91,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to cheer for \Nmy friends from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.39,0:14:41.31,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're no longer \Nallowed to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.95,0:14:45.79,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the room in the back\Nand write an essay of apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.79,0:14:48.78,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, you will play \Nin the individual tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.49,0:14:52.83,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi...  Chihaya...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.47,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Are you working hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.11,0:14:58.76,Chiha-overlap,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,One page should be enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.11,0:15:00.03,Chiha-main,Shi,0000,0000,0000,,So there won't be any more events today...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:00.03,Chiha-overlap,Sho,0000,0000,0000,,Quality over quantity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:00.71,push,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Can't they push the individual \Ntournament back a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.03,0:15:00.71,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.87,0:15:06.06,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I only ever run \Ninto them during matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:10.90,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Our opponent in the semifinals \Nwill be First Akashi Girls'.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.91,0:15:13.72,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that everybody \Nalready knows this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:16.64,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,but our biggest obstacle is \Nthe third-year Ousaka Megumu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:17.89,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.89,0:15:19.14,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.14,0:15:21.33,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the mind of an infant?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.33,0:15:23.48,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,She was the West representative \Nin last year's Queen match!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.48,0:15:26.10,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you watch Yumin's match with us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:30.30,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The girl who lost a close back-and-forth \Ngame to Yamamoto Yumi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:33.05,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,the strongest girl in western Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.12,0:15:35.44,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna play her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.06,0:15:39.54,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Their match was in a different area, \Nso I didn't get to watch them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.54,0:15:41.33,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,but Hanano-san helped scout them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:44.51,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,That's where these notes about \Nbags and straps came from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:47.21,pink,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls' all look ordinary\NGirl in front (with long hair)\NPink checkered handbag (Ponita)\Nwhite hand towel\Npink macaroon phone strap\NGirl with glasses \N(ordinary, sharp-tongued, popular)\Nblack handbag
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:46.35,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,This has nothing to do with karuta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.35,0:15:47.21,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:49.64,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.64,0:15:51.59,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see the cards \Nfrom my position!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.59,0:15:54.66,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I don't really understand \Nhow karuta works...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.66,0:15:55.60,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:15:57.99,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,You were very observant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.65,0:16:02.84,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,We can tell from these notes that, \Naside from Ousaka Megumu,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:06.22,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the others are ordinary girls who didn't \Nstart playing karuta until high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.79,0:16:08.91,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,They probably place more \Nemphasis on the meanings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:10.36,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,so they're probably good at love poems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.97,0:16:14.16,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Yuube-san is a little \Nboyish with simple taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:15.41,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,She might place more emphasis on sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.89,0:16:18.80,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,There's also their names.  \NMake sure you check their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.80,0:16:19.53,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Names?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.91,0:16:21.63,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,In Ousaka Megumu's case,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:24.61,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,she's probably good at "While it pains," \N"While it may," "While it brings," and "Long,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.61,0:16:26.18,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the cards with the starting sounds of her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.24,0:16:29.59,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,As for their order,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:31.92,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,the Class A players \NOusaka-san and Yuube-san
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:36.93,list,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,1. Yuube (Third-year) Class A\N2. Hayasaka (Second-year) Class B\N3. Ousaka (Third-year) Class A\N4. Nanase (Third-year) Class B\N5. Tanimura (Third-year) Class B
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:35.07,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,have been in these \Npositions every match,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:36.93,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,so it's likely that won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:40.45,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the best \Nscenario for us would be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.45,0:16:43.31,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid matching Ayase, Mashima,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.31,0:16:46.77,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and Porky against their Class A players.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:51.33,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,But our ace is aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.33,0:16:54.36,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,She wants to play strong opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.71,0:16:59.53,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.96,0:17:02.71,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Put me in the s-second position...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.03,0:17:08.45,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I've been in either the first \Nor third position every game,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.15,0:17:13.27,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll probably end up \Nagainst a Class B player
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.27,0:17:14.48,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,in the second position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.95,0:17:18.34,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya's thinking of our best chance to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.27,0:17:20.60,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,We only need two more victories...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.68,0:17:23.18,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,She's focused on being best in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.30,0:17:26.90,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.69,0:17:29.36,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Ayase,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.99,0:17:32.79,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,If you really want to win, \Nhere's my advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.95,0:17:35.54,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I've been meaning to talk \Nto you about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.03,0:17:37.45,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of our match against Hokuo,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.83,0:17:39.95,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,you surrendered a card because you \Nboth touched it at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.88,0:17:43.58,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,You can't give up when it's close.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:45.79,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to win, \Nyou have to fight for every card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:53.84,Chiha-main,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.53,0:17:56.43,Chiha-main,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,Win!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:17:59.80,Chiha-main,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have a repeat of the \NTokyo regional finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:03.81,Chiha-main-top,A,0000,0000,0000,,Will the semifinalist \Nteams please enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.35,0:18:10.36,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The semifinals:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:13.82,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School against \NFirst Akashi Girls' High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.14,0:18:17.89,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Fujisaki High School \Nagainst Hokuo Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.84,0:18:20.82,banner65,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Victory for Fujisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.97,0:18:23.29,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,I know that Fujisaki's famous, but \Ntheir supporters really stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:25.34,Chiha-main,Kame,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.34,0:18:26.96,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.96,0:18:28.71,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,Could you hold the other side for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.71,0:18:30.96,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to support Fujisaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:32.41,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.41,0:18:33.74,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.74,0:18:34.88,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,No good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:35.91,Chiha-main,Sudo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:37.72,Chiha-main,Yuri,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.83,0:18:42.14,victory,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Hokuo Victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.23,0:18:44.58,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Sudo-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.58,0:18:46.64,Chiha-internal,Kame,0000,0000,0000,,And all those alumni...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:58.97,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The Omi Jingu Learning Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:00.55,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The Urayasu room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.77,0:19:05.04,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,A new Master and Queen \Nare crowned here every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.42,0:19:09.98,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Where I played against \NShinobu-chan last summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.22,0:19:16.88,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the Queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.88,0:19:18.59,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,She was with someone from Fukui.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:27.59,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:30.75,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm putting Chihaya in the \Nnumber three position.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:31.27,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.16,0:19:33.64,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,In the regional final,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:35.78,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hokuo went with even \Nmatch-ups across the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.37,0:19:39.28,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Do we really want to \Ndodge our opponents?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:42.28,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya, you just have to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.43,0:19:44.36,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Bring home the win!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.09,0:19:46.33,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Victory for Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.72,0:19:47.49,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.26,0:19:54.99,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:59.96,list2,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(800,1)}1. Yuube (Third-year) Class A\N2. Hayasaka (Second-year) Class B\N3. Ousaka (Third-year) Class A\N4. Nanase (Third-year) Class B\N5. Tanimura (Third-year) Class B
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:58.49,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi Girls might \Nchange up their order.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.19,0:20:00.79,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mention this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.31,0:20:03.09,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mention this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:04.46,Chiha-internal,Both,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.07,0:20:08.80,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,They probably went with the \Nsame order every match
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.38,0:20:13.02,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,as preparation for the strong \Nteams they'll face from here on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.47,0:20:15.98,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,They'll switch it up once they \Nface a strong team.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:20.85,Chiha-internal,Both,0000,0000,0000,,So the question is whether Akashi \Nthinks we're good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.85,0:20:23.60,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,I will begin reading the order for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:26.39,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School versus \NFirst Akashi Girls' High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:28.95,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School, Nishida-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.43,0:20:31.71,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls', Yuube-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:33.71,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Good, all according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.11,0:20:36.08,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School, Oe-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:39.09,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls', Hayasaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:40.55,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,All according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.08,0:20:43.06,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School, Ayase-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.61,0:20:45.97,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls', Ousaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.54,0:20:47.60,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,All according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.07,0:20:50.12,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School, Mashima-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.73,0:20:53.06,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls', Nanase-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.35,0:20:56.44,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa High School, Komano-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:59.41,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,First Akashi Girls', Tanimura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.91,0:21:01.57,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,It's so exactly according to our plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.04,0:21:03.29,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,it's kind of sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.48,0:21:06.34,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Are they looking ahead to the finals?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.02,0:21:08.62,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,They don't respect us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.64,0:21:13.66,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.50,0:21:25.08,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,they have absolute faith \Nthat their ace will win?
